UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 154/GA
1 execute an election officer affirmation, on a form prescribed and furnished by the
2 State Board of Elections pursuant to administrative regulations promulgated under
3 KRS Chapter 13A, affirming the voter's identification as being personally known to
4 him or her. Once the affirmation is executed by the election officer, the voter shall
5 sign the precinct signature roster and shall proceed to cast his or her vote in a ballot
6 completion area. For purposes of this subsection, "personally known" means that
7 the election officer knows the voter's name and that the voter is a resident of the
8 community.
9 (5) The voter affirmation and the election officer affirmations executed under this
10 section shall be processed in the same manner as an oath of voter affidavit as
11 prescribed by KRS 117.245(3) and (4).
